<h2>Privacy Policy for weather.shaneburkhardt.com</h1>

<h3>Effective Date: May 23, 2025</h2>

<p>This Privacy Policy explains how weather.shaneburkhardt.com(&quot;we,&quot;
&quot;us,&quot; or &quot;our&quot;) handles personal information for California
residents. It covers the limited information we collect, why we collect it, and
your rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), as amended by the
California Privacy Rights Act (CPRA).</p>

<h3>Information We Collect</h3>

<p>Because this is a hobby weather website with no advertising,
we keep data collection to a minimum. We only collect information essential for
the website's operation and to understand how people use our site, so we can
improve it.</p>

<p>In the past 12 months, we have collected the following
categories of personal information:</p>

<ul>
 <li><b>Internet
     or other similar network activity:</b> This includes information about
     your interaction with our website, like the pages you visit, the time you
     spend on those pages, and your browser type. This is primarily collected
     through <b>Google Analytics</b> for website performance monitoring.</li>
 <li><b>Identifiers:</b>
     We collect your <b>Internet Protocol (IP) address</b> for website
     functionality and security, and it's also used by Google Analytics. Our
     website may also use <b>essential cookies</b> that help the site function
     correctly (e.g., remembering your preferred
     weather units or location). These cookies are strictly necessary for the
     operation of the site and do not collect personal data beyond what's
     needed for the site to work.</li>
</ul>

<p>We collect this information directly from your devices when
you use our website.</p>

<h3>How We Use Your Information</h3>

<p>We use the limited personal information we collect solely
for the following purposes:</p>

<ul>
 <li>To
     ensure the proper functioning and security of our website.</li>
 <li>To
     understand how our website is used (through Google Analytics)
     so we can improve its design and content.</li>
 <li>To
     personalize your experience on the site (e.g., remembering your preferred
     weather location or units through cookies).</li>
 <li>To
     comply with any legal obligations we may have.</li>
</ul>

<h3>How We Share Your Information</h3>

<p>We do not sell or share your personal information for
cross-context behavioral advertising.</p>

<p>The only third party we share information with is <b>Google
Analytics</b>. The data shared with Google Analytics is primarily aggregated
and anonymized, used to analyze website traffic and user behavior. While your
IP address is processed by Google Analytics, it's typically masked or
anonymized.</p>

<h3>Your California Privacy Rights</h3>

<p>As a California resident, you have specific rights regarding
your personal information:</p>

<ul>
 <li><b>Right
     to Know:</b> You can ask us to tell you what personal information we've
     collected about you, where it came from, why we collected it, and who
     we've shared it with.</li>
 <li><b>Right
     to Delete:</b> You can ask us to delete personal information we've
     collected from you, though some exceptions apply (like if we need it to
     keep the site running or for legal reasons).</li>
 <li><b>Right
     to Correct:</b> If you believe any of the personal information
     we hold about you is inaccurate, you have the right to ask us to correct
     it.</li>
 <li><b>Right
     to Opt-Out of Sale or Sharing:</b> Please note that we <b>do not sell or
     share</b> your personal information for cross-context behavioral
     advertising. Therefore, there is no &quot;Do Not Sell or Share My Personal
     Information&quot; link required.</li>
 <li><b>Right
     to Non-Discrimination:</b> We will not treat you differently for
     exercising any of your privacy rights.</li>
</ul>

<h3>How to Exercise Your Rights</h3>

<p>To exercise any of your rights, please contact us using one
of the methods below. Because of the limited personal information we collect,
the verification process will be simpler and typically involve confirming
details related to your website usage without requiring sensitive personal
data.</p>

<ul>
 <li><b>Email
     us at:</b><a href="mailto: weather@shaneburkhardt.com"> weather@shaneburkhardt.com</a></li>
</ul>

<p>We will acknowledge your request within 10 business days and
respond within 45 calendar days. If we need more time, we'll let you know.</p>

<h3>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h3>

<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we
do, we'll post the new policy on this page and update the &quot;Effective
Date&quot; at the top. We encourage you to review it periodically.</p>

<h3>Contact Us</h3>

<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our
privacy practices, please feel free to reach out: <a href="mailto:weather@shaneburkhardt.com">weather@shaneburkhardt.com</a></p>
